[
  {
    "text": "As an app developer, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=1"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's critical that you know exactly ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=2"
  },
  {
    "text": "what your app is storing on disk, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=4"
  },
  {
    "text": "where everything is being stored, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=6"
  },
  {
    "text": "and why it's needed. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=7"
  },
  {
    "text": "The best way to stay on top of these details ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "is to take inventory of what your app actually stores.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=11"
  },
  {
    "text": "To get started, build and run your app on a device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=17"
  },
  {
    "text": "then exercise all the features that will store things on disk. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=21"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once you've done this, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's time to look at what actually got stored, and where. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=26"
  },
  {
    "text": "Use the Devices and Simulators window in Xcode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=30"
  },
  {
    "text": "to extract your app's container so that we can see what's in it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=33"
  },
  {
    "text": "Select your device in the column on the left, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=38"
  },
  {
    "text": "then select your app in the Installed Apps list.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=41"
  },
  {
    "text": "And using the gear icon, choose Download Container, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=45"
  },
  {
    "text": "and save it on your Mac.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=48"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the Finder, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=53"
  },
  {
    "text": "Control-click on the xcappdata file that was downloaded. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=54"
  },
  {
    "text": "Choose Show Package Contents, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=59"
  },
  {
    "text": "and go into the App Data folder and start taking inventory. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=62"
  },
  {
    "text": "Look through the directories ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=66"
  },
  {
    "text": "to see what got stored in each one.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=68"
  },
  {
    "text": "For each file, make sure you can identify what it is, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=72"
  },
  {
    "text": "and why it's being stored. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you're not sure why something is there, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=77"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may be able to get rid of it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=80"
  },
  {
    "text": "You want to verify that you're putting the right files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=82"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the appropriate directories, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=84"
  },
  {
    "text": "and also consider whether the file should be included ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=86"
  },
  {
    "text": "in iTunes and iCloud backups. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=89"
  },
  {
    "text": "Only you can answer the first two questions, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=91"
  },
  {
    "text": "since they relate to your app's functionality. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll focus on the last two questions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "and start with where files should be stored. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=99"
  },
  {
    "text": "iCloud Drive is the best place to put documents ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=102"
  },
  {
    "text": "because they become available on all of the user's devices. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=105"
  },
  {
    "text": "Because the contents of your app's folder on iCloud Drive ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "is visible, it's important that you only put documents in there ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "that people will recognize and access directly. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=116"
  },
  {
    "text": "Your app reads and writes the content locally, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=120"
  },
  {
    "text": "and then the operating system will automatically upload ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=123"
  },
  {
    "text": "those files when the network is available. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=126"
  },
  {
    "text": "Since multiple devices may be accessing the files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "in iCloud Drive at the same time, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=132"
  },
  {
    "text": "you do need to use file coordination ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "to avoid any conflicts. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "So be sure to read the documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "for more details. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "For locally stored files, the Documents directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "is available in your app's container. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=145"
  },
  {
    "text": "Like with iCloud Drive, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "you should only store user-visible documents here. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=149"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once you have verified that your Documents directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=153"
  },
  {
    "text": "only contains files that should be exposed, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=156"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Files app can show them ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=159"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the On My iPhone or On My iPad location. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=161"
  },
  {
    "text": "To do this, your app should support Open in Place ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "and indicate that file sharing is enabled, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "both of which are configured in your Info.plist file. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "In addition to seeing their files in the Files app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=174"
  },
  {
    "text": "people can find their files in Spotlight, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=177"
  },
  {
    "text": "and on iPad, drag and drop them to other apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=180"
  },
  {
    "text": "Another great benefit of exposing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=184"
  },
  {
    "text": "your Documents directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=186"
  },
  {
    "text": "is that people will see their files in the Storage Settings UI ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=187"
  },
  {
    "text": "and can individually remove items. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=191"
  },
  {
    "text": "This makes it much easier to manage disk space, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=194"
  },
  {
    "text": "and will reduce the likelihood ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "that your entire app is deleted when space is low. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=198"
  },
  {
    "text": "But remember, the only things that should be going ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=202"
  },
  {
    "text": "into the Documents directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "are files that will make sense to people using your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=206"
  },
  {
    "text": "The critical question you should ask is, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=209"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Should my users be able to see this file?\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=212"
  },
  {
    "text": "If the answer is yes, then that's fine. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=215"
  },
  {
    "text": "But if the answer is no, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=218"
  },
  {
    "text": "move it out of the Documents directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=220"
  },
  {
    "text": "and into one of the following locations. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=222"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Application Support directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=225"
  },
  {
    "text": "is a good place to store files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=227"
  },
  {
    "text": "that might be in your Documents directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "but that shouldn't be seen by users. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=231"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, a database that your app needs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "but that the user would never open manually.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can store files at the top level, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=240"
  },
  {
    "text": "or you can create directories ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=242"
  },
  {
    "text": "if that helps keep things organized. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=243"
  },
  {
    "text": "The directory is completely under your control, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=246"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it's persistent. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=248"
  },
  {
    "text": "The contents are included in backups by default, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "but you can opt files out ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "if they don't need to be backed up. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "And finally, the disk space used ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the Application Support directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=260"
  },
  {
    "text": "is reported in the Storage Settings UI ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "under your app's Documents & Data total. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=265"
  },
  {
    "text": "The next location available to your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=268"
  },
  {
    "text": "is the Caches directory. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=270"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can store files here ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=272"
  },
  {
    "text": "that can be discarded if space is low. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=274"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is a good location for any content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=276"
  },
  {
    "text": "that can be re-downloaded when needed. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=278"
  },
  {
    "text": "The contents of the Caches directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=281"
  },
  {
    "text": "is not included in backups. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=283"
  },
  {
    "text": "When a device is low on disk space, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=285"
  },
  {
    "text": "iOS can help by clearing caches. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=288"
  },
  {
    "text": "Files will never be removed from your caches directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=291"
  },
  {
    "text": "if your app is running, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=294"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the operating system will start by clearing caches ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=296"
  },
  {
    "text": "for apps that haven't been used in a while. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=298"
  },
  {
    "text": "As a bonus to you, files in your caches directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=301"
  },
  {
    "text": "are not reported as part of your app's ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=304"
  },
  {
    "text": "Documents & Data total. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=307"
  },
  {
    "text": "Although they are included ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=308"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the overall space taken up by apps.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=310"
  },
  {
    "text": "And finally, you can put files that you won't need ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=313"
  },
  {
    "text": "for any extended period of time in the Temporary directory. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=316"
  },
  {
    "text": "Even though the operating system will periodically ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=320"
  },
  {
    "text": "remove these files when your app is not running, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's best to remove them when you're done with them.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "Like the Caches directory, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Temporary directory is not backed up ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=331"
  },
  {
    "text": "and is not reported in your app's Documents & Data total.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=333"
  },
  {
    "text": "These are all the common locations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=337"
  },
  {
    "text": "that your app can store files in. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=339"
  },
  {
    "text": "Use iCloud Drive and the Documents directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=341"
  },
  {
    "text": "for files that should be accessible in the Files app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=343"
  },
  {
    "text": "while application support, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=346"
  },
  {
    "text": "caches, and temporary directories ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=348"
  },
  {
    "text": "are all for use by your app privately. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=350"
  },
  {
    "text": "Be sure to review where you're storing things ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=353"
  },
  {
    "text": "and use the right directory. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=355"
  },
  {
    "text": "Lastly, a couple best practice tips. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you have files that don't need to be included ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=361"
  },
  {
    "text": "in iTunes or iCloud backups, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=363"
  },
  {
    "text": "use the NSFileManager APIs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=365"
  },
  {
    "text": "to set the \"IsExcludedFromBackupKey\". ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=368"
  },
  {
    "text": "You also want to be resilient to files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=372"
  },
  {
    "text": "that might be restored from an older version of your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=375"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, if you had a 32-bit version of your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=378"
  },
  {
    "text": "and its files were backed up, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=382"
  },
  {
    "text": "then for a 64-bit version of your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=384"
  },
  {
    "text": "those older files might get restored ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=387"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you need to be able to handle that situation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=389"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's best to use a versioning scheme on your files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=392"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that you can provide robust compatibility ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=395"
  },
  {
    "text": "across multiple versions of your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=397"
  },
  {
    "text": "And be sure that you're only storing files in one location. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=400"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=404"
  },
  {
    "text": "if you put files into your local Documents directory, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=405"
  },
  {
    "text": "don't duplicate those in iCloud Drive. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=408"
  },
  {
    "text": "Choose one place and stick to it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=411"
  },
  {
    "text": "For user documents, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=413"
  },
  {
    "text": "I suggest preferring a cloud storage location ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=415"
  },
  {
    "text": "unless you have a specific reason ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=417"
  },
  {
    "text": "to store files only local to a device.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=419"
  },
  {
    "text": "And finally, some new volume capacity details ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=425"
  },
  {
    "text": "are available in iOS 11 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "to help in knowing if it's a good time ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=430"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your app to take up more disk space.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first key, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=436"
  },
  {
    "text": "Available Capacity For Important Usage, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=437"
  },
  {
    "text": "indicates the amount of space that can be made available ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=440"
  },
  {
    "text": "for things that the user has explicitly requested ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=443"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your app's UI. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=446"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, if they have chosen to download a video ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=448"
  },
  {
    "text": "or a new level in a game. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=451"
  },
  {
    "text": "If the space you need is greater than what's available, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=454"
  },
  {
    "text": "you should let them know that their request ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=456"
  },
  {
    "text": "cannot be fulfilled. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=458"
  },
  {
    "text": "The second key, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=461"
  },
  {
    "text": "Available Capacity For Opportunistic Usage, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=462"
  },
  {
    "text": "indicates the amount of space available ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=465"
  },
  {
    "text": "for things that the user is likely to want, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=468"
  },
  {
    "text": "but hasn't explicitly requested. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=470"
  },
  {
    "text": "This could be something like the next episode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=473"
  },
  {
    "text": "in a series of videos that they are watching, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=475"
  },
  {
    "text": "or recently updated documents on a server ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=478"
  },
  {
    "text": "that they might be likely to open. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=480"
  },
  {
    "text": "For these types of files, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=482"
  },
  {
    "text": "you might store them initially in the Caches directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=484"
  },
  {
    "text": "until they are actually used, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=487"
  },
  {
    "text": "at which point you could move them ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=489"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the Application Support or Documents directory.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=490"
  },
  {
    "text": "After taking inventory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=495"
  },
  {
    "text": "and identifying what your app stored, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=496"
  },
  {
    "text": "if you found something that wasn't in the right place, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=498"
  },
  {
    "text": "then update your code to put it in the appropriate directory. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=501"
  },
  {
    "text": "And don't forget to add any necessary migration code ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=504"
  },
  {
    "text": "to move the files from one place to another. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=508"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you don't do this, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "you might inadvertently leave abandoned files behind. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=511"
  },
  {
    "text": "By cleaning up your on-disk storage, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=515"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can open up your Documents directory ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=517"
  },
  {
    "text": "to people in the Files app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=519"
  },
  {
    "text": "and they can be even more productive with your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=520"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can find more information at ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=523"
  },
  {
    "text": "developer.apple.com ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=525"
  },
  {
    "text": "or on our Developer Forums. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=526"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thanks for watching!",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-204/?time=528"
  }
]